de.ovgu.featureide.fm.core.functional

Interface Functional.IFunction<T,R>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Functional.IdentityFunction, Functional.NullFunction, Functional.ToCharSequenceFunction, Functional.ToStringFunction
    Enclosing class:
    Functional

    public static interface Functional.IFunction<T,R>
    Represents a function that takes one argument of type T and returns a result of type R.

    Example The following example shows a function which takes an integer and converts this integer to its string representation (Java 1.8 syntax used). IFunction<Integer, String> toString = (integer) -> { integer.toString() }; String seven = toString(7); // seven.equals("7")
    Since:
    3.0
    Author:
    Marcus Pinnecke
    See Also:
    Functional.map(Iterable, IFunction), Functional.join(Iterable, String, IFunction), Functional.join(Iterable, Object, IProvider, IFunction, IBinaryFunction), Object.equals(Object)
